Okay, let's break this down. My goal is to determine the current administrative unit for "Xã Ngư Lộc, Huyện Hậu Lộc, Tỉnh Thanh Hóa."  First, I'll confirm the province.  I know "Tỉnh Thanh Hóa" from my expertise, and after quickly checking the list of province resolutions, it looks like Thanh Hóa didn't undergo any province-level merges or name changes.  Good.

Now, on to the ward itself, "Xã Ngư Lộc."  I need to dig into the "Other Resolutions" list, particularly those related to Thanh Hóa.  Resolution "1686/NQ-UBTVQH15" looks promising, and sure enough, there it is!  Line 12 explicitly states that "Ngư Lộc" was merged with several other communes to form "Xã Vạn Lộc".  Bingo!

I need to make sure this new ward actually exists.  A quick check of the "New wards" list confirms the existence of  `{"ward_code":"16078","ward_name":"Xã Vạn Lộc","province_name":"Tỉnh Thanh Hóa"}`. Excellent.

Now, for the output.  The province is "Tỉnh Thanh Hóa," no change there.  The new ward is clearly "Xã Vạn Lộc" with a ward code of "16078," and I have a high degree of confidence in this result because the resolution directly addresses the merger. The citation will be pulled directly from the resolution and will include the relevant line for verification. It's a textbook case, really.
